fields.title: go down
fields.description: 杰克准备从一个n阶的楼梯上走下来,每一阶上都有一个分数,杰克一次可以跨任意阶(至少一阶),但是杰克有强迫症，他希望他每一次所站的台阶上的分数比他上一步所在的阶层的分数要高(比如他从第五阶跳到了第三阶,那么第三阶的分数要比第五阶的分数高才行)。现在杰克告诉你每一阶台阶上的分数,他想让你帮他算一下他从第n阶走到第1阶所能得到的分数最多是多少。

接下来是T组数据.

接下来是n个数,第i个数ai表示第i阶台阶的分数是ai(0<ai<10000).
(保证a1>an，所以杰克一定可以走到第一阶)
fields.output_description: 对于每组数据输出一个整数，表示杰克从第n阶走到第1阶所能获得的最大分数是多少。
fields.hint:
对于第一组样例，杰克可以走这几阶5->4->3->2->1这样他得到的分数是2+4+6+8+10=30

对于第二组样例，杰克可以走这几阶5->4->1 这样他得到的分数是15+9+1=25

fields.title: 斗地主
fields.description:
交大将要举行一次网上斗地主联赛，同学们很积极，现在已经有N个人报名参加联赛。我们知道，一场斗地主比赛需要3个人参加，但是同学之间有的是相互认识的，而有的不认识。 

如果3个人相互都认识，那么他们会很高兴地斗地主； 

如果3个人相互都不认识（即任意两个人都不认识），虽然不很尽兴，但也能公平地斗地主。 

但当3个人不是以上两种情况时，他们就会怀疑有人串通作弊而导致联赛不公平。考虑到这种情况，组委会决定不安排这样的三个人在一起斗地主。 

在N个参赛者中，原计划是每3个人都要进行一场比赛，因为上述原因，组委会想知道在避免被怀疑不公平的前提下，最多能进行多少场比赛呢？
fields.input_description:
输入包含多组测试数据（不超过10组）。 
每组数据第一行包含两个正整数N（3 <= N <= 1,000），M( 0 <= M <= 250,000)，分别表示参加比赛的人数和组委会获得的关系数目。 
接下来的M行中，每行包含两个正整数A和B（1 <= A, B <= N，且A不等于B），表示第A个人和第B个人是相互认识的，注意：认识的关系是没有传递性的，例如A认识B，B认识C，但A不一定认识C；而且，由于组委会的消息来源很多，所以输入的认识关系可能有重复，并且类似“1，2”和“2，1”这种情况是等价的。
fields.output_description: 对于每一组测试数据，输出占一行，输出可以举行的比赛的场数。
fields.hint: 对于第1组，总共可以举行2场，即<1,3,4>和<2,3,4>.

fields.title: 补兵
fields.description:
在非常流行的DOTA游戏中，补兵是非常重要的一种技术统计。如果一个单位被对方的多个单位攻击至死，则对该单位造成最后一次（致命的）伤害的攻击者将会获得更多的奖励（金钱和经验），这名攻击者被记录一次补兵。 

现在有N个人（编号为1、2、...、N）攻击对方的一个单位。假设每人每次攻击的伤害和每两次攻击之间的间隔都是固定的。输入将给出每个人两次攻击之间的间隔时间，并假设每个人第一次攻击的时刻值就是他的两次攻击之间的时间间隔值。例如，一个人攻击间隔为2，则他会在时刻2、4、6、8……进行攻击。时间以整数计算。 

如果多个人同时攻击导致对方死亡，攻击伤害最大的那个被记录一次补兵。如果攻击伤害最大的不止一个，则其中编号最小的人被记录一次补兵。 

一个单位血量小于等于0就被判为死亡。 

你的任务是求出对方单位死亡的时刻和被记录一次补兵的那个人的编号。
fields.input_description:
输入的第一行包含一个整数M (1 < M ≤ 100)，表示测试数据的组数。 
每组数据第一行包含两个整数N (2 ≤ N ≤ 1000)和H (1 < H ≤ 1000000)，表示攻击对方某个单位的人数和对方单位的血量。 
接下来有N行，每行两个整数，分别表示每个人每次攻击的伤害A (1 ≤ A ≤ 100)，以及每两次攻击之间的间隔T (1 ≤ T ≤ 100)。
fields.output_description: 对每组数据，输出一行，对方单位死亡的时刻和被记录一次补兵的那个人的编号，用空格隔开。
fields.hint: 输入数据较多，尽量用scanf和printf代替cin和cout。

fields.title: 反向匹配串
fields.description:
冬瓜和界面熊非常喜欢研究一些奇奇怪怪的问题，由于界面熊的数学很好，所以冬瓜问他的问题一向不会是数学题。这天，冬瓜又来刁难界面熊。 

冬瓜从口袋里拿出了三张卡片，每张上面有且只有一个字符串，分别是"usedrose", "yeahpeng", “afterstory”。冬瓜说：我现在想让你找出所有的反向配对串。所谓反向配对串，如果我们另”usedrose”为字符串A，则串A的转置A*=“esordesu”，如果还有另外一个串B，只要满足A的字典序大于B，且A*的字典序小于B*的话，我们则称A、B为一对反向配对串。 

界面熊：不就三张卡片嘛，我一个个数不就完了。一个、两个…… 

这时冬瓜从另一个口袋里掏出了一沓卡片.............

fields.output_description: 输入一个整数 R，为在N个卡片中，一共有多少对反向匹配串。

fields.title: Orsum again

yeahpeng被一道关于异或的题困扰了许久，现在，他向你寻求帮助。

为了输入方便，令x = (a * Li + b) %(n+1), y = (c * Ri + d) % (n + 1) 

L(i+1) = min(x, y) 

R(i+1) = max(x,y)

fields.title: 分狗粮
fields.description: 今天handsomehow给大家发了n包狗粮,每一包狗粮里面装有a颗狗粮.而现在你需要把这n包狗粮平均分成4份,以便你和你的室友享用,并且不能把包装给拆开.问你是否能够平均分给你的室友,并且没有剩余?
fields.input_description:
第一行是一个整数T,表示数据组数.
接下来有T组数据.
每组数据的开头是一个整数n(4<=n<=20),表示有n包狗粮,接着n个数代表每包狗粮的颗数.
保证每包狗粮的颗数a满足条件1<=a<=10,000
fields.output_description:
如果能够均分一行输出yes
否则输出一行no
fields.hint:
对于第二组数据,你可以这样分(1,7),(2,6),(3,5),(2,4,2),刚好每人8颗.

对于第一组数据,你不能将他们平均分成4堆.(将会有剩余)

fields.title: SSR，我也一定能出的
fields.description:
有一天，HandsomeHow发现竹子在玩阴阳师，但是竹子一直没有SSR所以快要对这个游戏绝望了，HandsomeHow得知以后决定给竹子两张超级符咒，这种符咒只能抽出SR和SSR，并且连续两次出的级别是不会相同的，也就是说，竹子肯定会抽出一张SR和一张SSR，现在我们要来重现一下竹子抽卡的画面。

你需要编写一个程序，你的程序会被运行2次，每一次的输入都是"GO"，代表着竹子要抽卡了。

你需要第一次输出"bamboo gets SR!"， 第二次输出"bamboo gets SSR!"
fields.input_description: 一行  GO
fields.output_description:
对于第一个测试文件输出   bamboo gets SR!
对于第二个测试文件输出   bamboo gets SSR!
fields.hint: 你的程序会被同时运行2次

fields.title: 银河铁道之夜
fields.description:
在银河之中穿梭的列车上，乔班尼和柯贝内拉看着窗外的景色止不住的赞叹，没有比这更加美丽，更加灿烂的景色了，但让人难过的是，列车终将会到站，柯贝内拉马上就会离开乔班尼的身边了，去向冥河的另一边，再也回不来了

“明明，明明是我先来的，不管是遇见心叶也好，写故事也好，投稿也好，明明都是我先来的，事情为什么会变成这样呢？”合上书本，美羽叹了一口气，“既然这样，那么在离开之前，远子学姐，请你回答我最后一个问题好吗？”

“好的”远子学姐撕下一页书送进嘴里。

“列车在经过半人马阿尔法星车站的时候会进行转车，需要将到达的乘客按次序分配车厢，现在有n批乘客到达车站，每批乘客的人数为ai，需要将他们安排在一列有m个车厢的列车中，同一批乘客只能分配在同一个车厢中，并且不能打乱乘客之间的顺序，如果想要最多的车厢中人最少，请问应该怎样安排，最多的车厢中有多少人？”

（突然懵逼的远子学姐）

那边那个，没错，别看了说的就是你，过来回答一下这个问题。
fields.input_description:
第一行是一个整数T,表示数据组数.
接下来是T组数据.
每组数据的一开始是两个整数n(1<=n<=10000),m(1<=m<=10000)，表示总共有n批乘客，列车有m个车厢。
接下来一行有n个数$a_{1},a_{2}....a_{n}$( 1<=$a_{i}$ <= 10000)，$a_{i}$表示第i批乘客的人数
fields.output_description: 对于每组数据输出一个整数，表示人数最多的车厢中有多少人。
fields.hint:
对于第一组样例，将所有的乘客安排在第一个车厢

对于第二组样例，将第一批和第二批乘客安排在第一个车厢，第三批乘客安排在第二个车厢

fields.title: 巧克力小姐的大惊小怪
fields.description:
又一次，国服的活动在错误的时间点开始了，但这样不也很好吗？不用在情人节的时候窝在家里刷活动而是可以出门去吃狗粮了（并不）。总之，，各位masta准备好苹果和肝了吗？

在情人节活动中，咕哒子能够通过任务获取巧克力硬币，然后使用巧克力硬币去兑换servent们赠送的巧克力（为简化问题，巧克力硬币都是相同的），可以从每位servent那里兑换最多一个巧克力，咕哒子一共有n种servent（i = 1,2,3....n），第i种servent有ai个，第i位servent的巧克力需要bi个硬币兑换，而收到第i位从者的巧克力，会让咕哒子增加ci点的“混乱邪恶度”，现在已经知道在整个活动过程中一共能获得m个巧克力硬币，请问，咕哒子的“混乱邪恶度”最高能达到多少？

（尼禄沉船……消沉中）
fields.input_description:
第一行是一个整数T,表示数据组数.
接下来是T组数据.
每组数据的一开始是两个整数n(1<=n<=200),m(1<=m<=200)，表示总共有n种servent，一共能获得巧克力硬币。
接下来n行每行有三个数$a_{i}$(1 <= $a_{i}$ <= 200)，$b_{i}$(1 <= $b_{i}$ <= 200)，$c_{i}$(1 <= $c_{i}$ <= 200)，$a_{i}$表示第i种servent的个数，$b_{i}$表示兑换第i种servent的巧克力需要多少个巧克力硬币，$c_{i}$表示兑换之后增加的混乱邪恶度
fields.output_description: 对于每组数据输出一个整数，表示咕哒子最大的“混乱邪恶度”。
fields.hint:
对于第一组样例，兑换第一种和第二种从者的巧克力各一个，20*1+10*1=30

对于第二组样例，兑换两个第二种从者的巧克力，10*0+20*2=40

fields.title: 抽卡的秘诀
fields.description:
今天，竹子很开心，因为他在玩阴阳师的时候抽到了SSR，但是他现在有很多多余的符咒。

竹子把这些符咒排成一排，并给每一个符咒一个可爱值。

第$i$个符咒的可爱值为$cute_{i}$

现在竹子给你k个数$a_{1},a_{2}\cdots a_{k}$，他想问你对于每一个$a_{i}$,有多少对{l,r}(1<=l<=r<=n),能使得

$cute_{l}\ xor\ cute_{l+1}\ xor\ \cdots\ xor\ cute_{r}\  = a_{i}$.

其中xor为按位异或运算.
fields.input_description:
数据的第一行是一个整数T(T<=5)
接着是T组数据。
对于每一组数据，第一行是一个整数n(2<=n<=10000),表示竹子拥有的符咒的数量。
第二行是n个整数:$cute_{1},cute_{2}.....cute_{n}$,($0<=cute_{i}<=1000000$)。
接着是一个整数k,(1<=k<=1000)
最后一行是k个整数$a_{1},a_{2}.....a_{n}$,($0<=a_{i}<=1000000$)。
fields.output_description: 对于每一组数据，输出k行，每行一个数，表示在cute序列中能找到多少对{l,r}满足题目描述的条件。
fields.hint:
对于样例,对于$a_{1}$=1,我们可以找到{1,1},{2,2},{2,4},{4,5}这样4对满足条件

cute[1] = 1; cute[2] = 1; cute[2] xor cute[3] xor cute[4] = 1; cute[4] xot cute[5] = 1

fields.title: 找众数
fields.description: 给你一个长度为n序列，请你找出这里面的众数(出现次数最多的数)
fields.input_description:
数据的第一行是一个整数T(T<=100)
接着是T组数据。
对于每一组数据，第一行是一个整数n(1<=n<=100),表示竹子拥有的符咒的数量。
第二行是n个整数:$v_{1},v_{2}.....v_{n}$,($0<=v_{i}<=100$)。
fields.output_description: 对于每一组数据，输出一行一个众数。如果有多个众数，则输出任意一个。
fields.hint:
对于第一组样例，2出现了2次，最多。

对于第二组样例，1和2都出现了2次，输出1和2均可

fields.title: Knapsack Problem
fields.description:
Today $HH$ becomes a shopper, and he wants to buy a lot.

 

$HH$ has a bag that can carry at most $w$ kilograms things in total, and he has $d$ dollars.

 

Now he wants to buy $n$ items，the $i^{th}$ item weights $w_i$ kilogram and costs $c_i$ dollars.

 

$HH$is not good at math so he asks you to tell him whether he can buy all the things and carry them with the bag.
fields.input_description:
The first line contains an positive integer $T(1 \leq T \leq 10)$, represents there are $T$ test cases.

For each test case:

The first line contains three positive integers $n,w,d(1 \leq n \leq 100,1 \leq w \leq 100,1 \leq d \leq 100)$ - the number of items $HH$ wants to buy, the max weight that his bag can carry, and the money he has.

The second line contains $n$ integers $w_1,w_2\ldots w_n$($1\leq w_i \leq 100$).

The third line contains $n$ integers $c_1,c_2\ldots c_n$($1\leq c_i \leq 100$).
fields.output_description: For each test case, output one line "YES" (without quotes) if $HH$ is possible to buy all the items and carry them in his bag, and "NO" (without quotes) otherwise.
fields.hint: In the first example all the items cost $17$ dollars in total and weight $12$ kilograms in total, $HH$ has enough money and his bag can carry $12$ kilogram things.

fields.title: 不再孤独的HandsomeHow
fields.description: 不再孤独的HandsomeHow
fields.input_description: 不再孤独的HandsomeHow
fields.output_description: 不再孤独的HandsomeHow

fields.title: Tickets
fields.description: Bamboo want to buy a ticket cost P. she can buy the ticket by app and get a concession to D. At the same time, she can appoint an agent and have different discount. Please tell her what kind of way is most economical and the minimum cost. Print the first way if there is more than one possibility.
fields.input_description:
Input contains multiple test cases. 
The first line of each test contains three integers P, D, n. (1 <= P, D <= 1e9, 1 <= n <= 1e5), the ticket price, the concession of app and the number of agent.
The second n line contains a real number a[i], the discount of i th agent.
fields.output_description: For each test case, print a line. Print “APP” if buy ticket by app or print the agent’s order if buy ticket by appoint an agent. And an integer means the minimum cost, keeping two decimal places.

fields.title: Wave string
fields.description:
There is a kind of string called “wave string”. If str is made as s1s2s3...sL-1sLsL-1sL-2...s2s1s2s3...., we will call it “wave string” and s1s2s3...sL and sLsL-1...s1 are its waves and they must appear alternately.

For example, “abc”, “abcba”, “abcbabc”,”abcbabcba”... are wave strings. But they have different number of wave, “abc” have 1 wave, “abcba” have 2 waves(abc,cba), “abcbabc” have 3 waves(abc,cba,abc).

Now, s is a string of lenth n(s1s2s3s4s5...sn), and str is a wave string which is a substring of s(sisi+1si+2...si+m-1) . We have known i and L and we want to know the maxium number of wave str have.
fields.input_description:
Input contains multiple test cases. 
Each test case: 
The first line is a string s (1<= |s| <= 10^6)
The second line is a integer k (1 <= k <= 10^5)
The next k lines, each line is i and L, (1<= i <=|s|,2 <= L <=10^4).
fields.output_description: k lines, each lines is the maxium number of wave str have.

fields.title: The road ahead to be boundless
fields.description: We will find life is difficult and run into a stone wall sometimes. But we must go ahead because there is no way to turn back. Recently in the last Labor Day, UsedRose and Yeah with some friends went to park. Unfortunately they were trapped by a storm. So they must drive back to school. But they only have one car and the car can take two people at most. The important thing is that the car’s speed depend on the person who is the slowest in the car. They are a team, so they ask for your help to let all people go back to school as soon as possible.
fields.input_description:
Input contains multiple test cases. 
Each test case contains an integer n (1<=N<=10000),m(999 <= m <= 999999),Said a total of N people to cross the river.and the length of river is m.
Next row contains n integers ni, show the i-th people’s speed that he can accept max .(1 <= ni <= 1000)
fields.output_description: For each test case, Print a line, the times of everyone can go back to school(round up to an integer) and make as soon as possible.

fields.title: King’s Knight
fields.description:
Long time ago, there was a powerful magic kingdom. The king led his Knights to go on an expedition in order to acquire more treasure. When they came back, the king decided to reward the Knights who fought for him.

The king declared that every Knight would gain A coins during the first year. Every year after the first year the gold they would gain are Q times as many as the last year. Could you please help the Knights count how many coins would they gain N years later？(The answer must be very large, so give the answer module M)

(1<=T<=50,1<=A<=500,1<=Q<=500,2<=M<=10^9+7,1<=P<=1000)
fields.input_description:
The first line of the input contains integer t ? the number of the test cases
For each case:
The first line of the input contains three integers A, Q, M ? the gold of the first year, the number of the multiple and the modulus.
The second line of the input contains a P-digits Big Integer n ? the number of years
fields.output_description: For each case there must be an integer. The answer that module M.

fields.title: DaVinci code
fields.description:
DaVinci Code is a famous novel which is written by Dan Brown. And a DaVinci Code Tube is a lock that has five code wheels. Only you put the code wheels into a right order, could you open the lock. Catfish is a person who is very curious. So after a few days, he finally made one, which is different from that one in the novel. The tube he made has only four Alphabet code wheels, and each wheel only contains eight characters in upper case. They are ‘A’,’B’,’C’,’D’,’E’,’F’,’G’ and ‘H’. In order to open the code tube, you have to put the code wheel to the right order. Each time, you could add or minus 1 to any character. When add 1 to ‘H’, the character will change to ‘A’ and minus 1 to ‘A’, the character will change to ‘H’. You could also exchange the character with its neighbor. Each action will cost one step. Catfish wants to know that how can we use minimum number of steps to open the code tube.

(1<=t<=20)
fields.input_description:
The first line of the input contains integer t ? the number of the test cases
For each case:
The first line of the input contains four characters ? the beginning of the code tube
The second line of the input contains four characters ?the password of the code tube
fields.output_description: For each case there must be an integer. The minimum number of steps

fields.title: Legend of the Galactic Heroes
fields.description:
“There are something can be done, something can’t.”

In 799 years of The Milky Calendar, Yang Wen-li commanded the Iserlohn Fleet to defense the Reinhard’s attack. Yang deeply understands the enemy is stronger than his fleet. The idea here is to avoid a head on battle with a strong enemy, and instead strike at his weakness elsewhere. The emperor fleet was divided into n parts, named 1,2,3…n from left to right. The numbers of warships in i th fleet is ai. Similarly, Yang sent out n fleets and the numbers is bi.(|ai|,|bi| <= 1e4)

M messages formatted “l r k” about battlefield were sent to Flagship Hyperion and they are sorted in time-ordered. The massage expresses “k is the sum of emperor’s fleets subtract the sum of Yang’s in [l,r]”.But the information passing sometimes make mistakes. The task is checking messages and tell Yang how many conflicts happen(You can ignore the messages have conflicts with previous messages). The fate of Yang’s Fleet depends on you, go for it!
fields.input_description:
Input contains multiple test cases.
The first line of each test contains two integers n, m. (1 <= n <= 1e5,1 <= m <= 1e4)
The following m lines have three integer l, r, k (1 <= l <= r <= n, |k| <= 1e9)
fields.output_description: For each test case, Print a integer, the numbers of conflicts.

fields.title: White album 2
fields.description:
“Why is it go? ...For the first time having a person I love, and a person who can be lifetime friend. Two piece of happiness come together, and they bring more happiness to me. What I get should be wonderful time like a dream. But why is it go?”

The “happiness” has a value called “favor degree”. One piece of happiness can bring more happiness. Unfortunately, Touma can only choose one of them. She can choose different happiness to get if she gets the same happiness twice or more. Touma knows the happiness’ “favor degree” and some information meaning happiness A can brings happiness B. How much “favor degree” Touma can get? And, if Touma gets the same happiness more than once, the “favor degree” will only be counted once. At first time Touma have the 1th Happiness.
fields.input_description:
Input contains multiple test cases. 
The first line of each test contains two integers n, m. (1 <= n <= 1e4, 1 <= m <= 1e5),n is the number of happiness, m is the number of information.
The second line contains n integers v[i], the “favor degree” of i th happiness.(0 < v[i] <= 1e4)
The following m lines have three integer a, b (1 <= a, b <= n), meaning happiness a can bring happiness b.
fields.output_description: For each test case, Print a integer, the maximum “favor degree” Touma can get.

fields.title: Put an elephant into a refrige
fields.description:
Yesterday when i had a talk with my bamboo, he said that he went hunting recently and harvest the highly. So he wants to have a party, but he has too much dead elephant. Fortunately,he also has many refrigerators, and he want to put everyone elephant into a refrigerator. Elephants were put on an X-coordinate axis. The i-th elephant's coordinate is Xi meters. Bamboo can only put an elephant into a refrigerator once, and his start position is the point in the x-coordinate axis. Putting an elephant into a refrigerator does not cost time, but every elephant will decay if it isn’t in the refrigerator, and the i-th elephant has a decay speed vi.

Now he wants to let the sum of elephants decay is minimum. Would you please calculate the minimum decay of all elephants?
fields.input_description:
Input contains multiple test cases. 
Each test case contains two integers N (1<= N <= 2000),V(V > 0),X(x > 0),represents the number of elephants, the speed and start position of bamboo.
Then N lines followed. Each line contains two integers Xi ( Xi >= 0 ), Yi(Yi >=0),which showed i-th elephant’s position and decay speed.
fields.output_description: For each test case, Print a line, the sum of decay that is minimum.

fields.title: Buy buy buy
fields.description:
yeahpeng like apple very much. One day, he comes to the street of apple and so many watermelons which make him want to "buy buy buy". But, he cant not buy all because of money. So, he makes a rule to buy watermelons.

There are n stores on the street. yeahpeng will start at the first store and end in the last store. And he will buy one or zero watermelon in every store and never turn back.

Every watermelon has its price p and weight w. If the price of previous in jth store he buy is pj and the next one in ith store is pi, there mush be i > j and pi - ki <= pj <= pi + ki, the first watermelon he could buy in any store.

yeahpeng want to get the maximum sum of weight.
fields.input_description:
Input contains multiple test cases. 
Each test case: 
Begin with an integer n(1 <= n <= 30000), 
n lines follow, each with three integers: pi wi ki (1 <= pi <= 10^10, 1 <= wi <= 10^6, 1 <= ki <= 10^10)
fields.output_description: One line: the maximum sum of weight

fields.title: Escape from the earth
fields.description: It is said that the doomsday will come and earth would be destroyed. n people want to escape from earth. There are m stars can be arrived. Moreover, some of them are suitable for a particular person. Within the limit of resource, i th star’s maximum capacity is ai. Can you find a feasible solution to make everyone arrive a star suit him?
fields.input_description:
Input contains multiple test cases.
The first line of each test contains two integers n, m. (1 <= n <= 1e5, 1 <= m <= 10), the number of people and the number of stars.
The second n line contains m integers k [i, j], k [i, j] = 1 means star j suit person i and k [i, j] = 0 means unsuitable.
The last line have m integer a[i] (1 <= a[i] <= 1e5), meaning star i ’s maximum capacity is a[i].
fields.output_description: For each test case, Print a line “YES” if everyone can arrive a star suit him and “NO” if can’t.

fields.title: Alpha and Beta
fields.description:
Alpha and Beta are best friends and make company with each other all the time.

There is a time when a game called “make pairs” gains much popularity. Alpha and Beta are very fond of it and like to invite you to play with them.

Given a string, which is simply composed of either A or B, they want to know how many AB pairs can Alpha and Beta find in that string. Can you help them?

A pair is legal if and only if A appears at first, and whether B is near to A is not required. In other words, B makes pair with A which is nearest before B, and they both can be used only once.
fields.input_description: There are a series of strings. The length of each string is less than 1000.
fields.output_description:
For each case, if there is none legal pair that they can find, print -1. Otherwise, print the number of them.
Please note the output format.

fields.title: Ranking Problem
fields.description:
If you are a LOLer, then you must be very familiar with LPL league. In the spring of 2016 LPL league game to take the points system, if a team won in BO3, then increase 1 point, failure does not buckle points, followed by each team based on the standings, the higher the ranking the higher the points, the same points if the same rank.Then only if there are n teams participating, the total number of cases the ranking in the game?

For example, 2 teams ranking has 3 ways.

1. Both first

2. team A first and team B second

3. team B first and team A second
fields.input_description: Input consists of several datasets. Each of them has a single integer number n (1 ≤ n ≤ 1000) ― the number of LPL teams.
fields.output_description: For each case, print the number of cases the ranking in the game. The result can be very large, print the result modulo 2016515.

fields.title: Juju's lessons
fields.description: Juju is a child who enjoys learning. she has two majors and many courses have time conflict.As a child who love to learn, she wants to take lessons as many as she can. There are each lesson's start time and end time. She wants to know how many lessons can be taked after she master the replication.
fields.input_description:
Input contains multiple test cases. 
The first line of each test case contains one interger n(1 <= n <= 100),the numbers of lesson.
Next n lines have two integers a, b. (1 <= a < b <= 1000),the start time and the end time of each lesson.
fields.output_description: For each test case, Print a line, the numbers of lessons she can take.

fields.title: Piece of Cake
fields.description:
The annual neonatal trials will start next week, at the same time, all old guys of the ACM teams want to reward all M students who work hard in the match. So, we buy N cakes which are of different radius. Consider the height of each cake is 1.

However, Master Ye consider that every student should assign to the equal size of cake, which means every cake assigned to students should be the same volume. Also, he mentions, one student should assign only one piece of cake.

Master Ye want you to calculate the maximum volume that every student can get. Can you help him figure out this problem?
fields.input_description:
The first line contain the number of test cases,no more than 20.
The second line contain two integers,1 ≤ N, M ≤ 65536 which means the number of cakes and students
Then following one line contain N integers represent each cake’s radius,and 1 ≤ r ≤ 65536.
fields.output_description: For each test case, output one line with the largest possible volume V such that me and my friends can all get a pie piece of size V. The answer should be given as a floating point number correct to three decimal places;

fields.title: How many primes
fields.description:
A prime number (or a prime) is a natural number greater than 1 that has no positive divisors other than 1 and itself. For example, 5 is prime because 1 and 5 are its only positive integer factors, whereas 6 is composite because it has the divisors 2 and 3 in addition to 1 and 6.

Prime looks so lonely because it only has a few factors. That is the reason Junko show special preference to the prime. Now, She wants to know how many primes in [l, r].
fields.input_description:
Input contains multiple test cases. 
Each test case contains two integers l, r. (1 <= l <= r <= 1,000,000)
fields.output_description: For each test case, Print a line, the numbers of prime in [l, r].

fields.title: Yeahpeng's inequality
fields.description:
Yeahpeng is not good at inequality. Unfortunately, there are many inequalities in his homework and they make him be in trouble. Cornered yeah wants your help.

There are n inequalities in total and the form is:

Op x

Op is one of {>=, >, =, <, <=}, x is an integer. What he wants to know is how many inequalities can be satisfied at most in the first i inequalities.

fields.title: Knapsack Problem
fields.description:

Now he wants to buy $n$ items，the $i^{th}$ item weights $w_i$ kilogram and costs $c_i$ dollars.

fields.title: HGCD
fields.description:
$HH$ is learning $GCD$ today, $GCD$ is short for $Greatest \ Common \ Divisor$.  You can look at this implementation:

long long gcd(long long a, long long b){
	while(a > 0 && b > 0){
	    a %= b;
	    swap(a , b);
	}
	return a + b;
}

But $HH$ is so careless that he changes "%" into "-", let's call this new funtion $HH's \ Greatest \ Common \ Divisor $ ($HGCD$). You can look at this implementation:

long long hgcd(long long a, long long b) {
    while (a > 0 && b > 0) {
        a -= b;
        swap(a , b);
    }
    return a + b;
}

Now $HH$ run $HGCD(a,b)$ for all $1 \leq a \leq n$, $1 \leq b \leq n$,$HH$ wants to know how many times does his algorithm - $HGCD$ works correctly.

It's guaranteed that long long is enough for this problem.
fields.hint: In the first example, we have $gcd(a,b) == hgcd(a,b)$ for all $1 \leq a \leq 3, 1 \leq b \leq 3$ except $a = 2, b = 3)$

fields.title: Music Problem
fields.description:
Listening to the music is relax, but for obsessive(强迫症), it may be unbearable.

$HH$ is an obsessive, he only start to listen to music at $12:00:00$, and he will never stop unless the song he is listening ends at integral points (both minute and second are $0$ ), that is, he can stop listen at $13:00:00$ or $14:00:00$,but he can't stop at $13:01:03$ or $13:01:00$, since $13:01:03$ and $13:01：00$ are not an integer hour time.

Now give you the length of some songs, tell $HH$ whether it's possible to choose some songs so he can stop listen at an integral point, or tell him it's impossible.

Every song can be chosen at most once.

fields.output_description: For each test case, output one line "YES" (without quotes) if $HH$ is possible to stop listen at an integral point, and "NO" (without quotes) otherwise.

In the second example if we choose the first and the third songs, they cost $3600$ seconds in total, so $HH$ can stop at $13:00:00$

In the third example if we choose the first and the second songs, they cost $7200$ seconds in total, so $HH$ can stop at $14:00:00$

fields.title: Shortest Path
fields.description:
Today $HH$ becomes a designer, and he faces a problem so he asks you for help.

$Treeisland$ is a country with $n$ cities and $n - 1 $ two-way road and from any city you can go to any other cities.

$HH$ the designer is going to design a plan to divide $n$ city into $n/2$ pairs so that the sum of the length between the $n/2$ pairs city is minimum.

Now $HH$ has finished it but he doesn't know whether it's true so he ask you to calculate it together.

It's guaranteed that $n$ is even.

Then $n-1$ lines followed.

Each line contains three positive integer $u$, $v$ and $len$, $(u \neq v, 1 \leq u \leq n,1 \leq v \leq n,1 \leq len \leq 10^9)$indicating there is a road of length $len$ between $u$ and $v$. 

It's guarantee you can get to any city from any city.
fields.output_description: For each test case, output in one line an integer, represent the minimum sum of length.
fields.hint:

fields.title: Maximize The Beautiful Value
fields.description:
Today $HH$ finds a non-decreasing sequence$(a_1,a_2....a_n, a_i \leq a_{i+1})$, he thinks it's not beautiful so he wants to make it beautiful.

To make it, $HH$ will choose exactly one number and move it forward at least $k$ steps(i.e. you can move $a_i$ to $a_j$ if $k \leq i - j$), and then he defines the beautiful value $F(n)$ as $\sum_{i=1}^n{i \times a_i}$.


$HH$ asks you to calculate $max(F(n))$

fields.hint:
In the first example, you can move the fifth number $4$ for $3$ steps and make the sequence become [$4,1,1,3,5$], then the beautiful value is $4 \times 1 + 1 \times 2 + 1 \times 3 + 3 \times 4 + 5 \times 5 = 46$.

You can also move the fifth number to make it become [$1,5,1,3,4$], the beautiful value is also 46.

In the second example, you can move the  fifth number $5$ for $2$ steps and make the sequence become [$1,1,5,3,4$]

In the second example, you can move the  second number $1$ for $1$ steps and then the sequence is still [$1,1,3,4,5$]

scanf is commended。

fields.title: HGCD
fields.description:
$HH$ is learning $GCD$ today, $GCD$ is short for $Greatest \ Common \ Divisor$.  You can look at this implementation:

long long gcd(long long a, long long b){
	while(a > 0 && b > 0){
	    a %= b;
	    swap(a , b);
	}
	return a + b;
}

But $HH$ is so careless that he changes "%" into "-", let's call this new funtion $HH's \ Greatest \ Common \ Divisor $ ($HGCD$). You can look at this implementation:

long long hgcd(long long a, long long b) {
    while (a > 0 && b > 0) {
        a -= b;
        swap(a , b);
    }
    return a + b;
}

Now $HH$ run $HGCD(a,b)$ for all $1 \leq a \leq n$, $1 \leq b \leq n$,$HH$ wants to know how many times does his algorithm - $HGCD$ works correctly. 

Note:

void swap(long long &a, long long &b){
    long long t = a;
    a = b; b = t;
}
fields.input_description:
The first line of input will contain an integer $T$($1 \leq T \leq 5$),denoting the number of test cases. 
For each test case:
The first and only line contains an integer $n$ ($1 \leq n \leq 10^{12}$)
fields.output_description:
For every test case output the number of times $gcd(a,b) == hgcd(a,b)$
It's guaranteed that long long is enough for this problem.
fields.hint: In the first example, we have $gcd(a,b) == hgcd(a,b)$ for all $1 \leq a \leq 3, 1 \leq b \leq 3$ except $a = 2, b = 3)$
